reviewText: Good quality. Just what I expected.

This is one of my favorite childhood cartoons! I enjoyed every minute watching it. The cartoon DVD doesn't have English subtitles, but I don't think it makes a problem watching it, since there isn't much talk in the cartoon - like in "Tom and Jerry" you can guess what's happening without a translation. I used to always laugh at the two little mice in the cartoon who play tricks on a good friendly cat Leopold, but eventually get trapped themselves in their tricks, and sometimes felt bad for them though they're not pictured as positive characters. It's a good cartoon to watch for kids and for adults (who like cartoons) because though it's funny it has a morale in it that everyone should be friendly and live in peace!
my daughter like it but she does not understand russian, but it was still something good to remember from way back, i love it, thank you for having it
